  "texts": [
    "It encompasses a practical understanding of how the world works and is considered a shared and implicit awareness.",
    "For instance, when people discuss sunrise and sunset, it is a natural and common understanding that the sun rises in the east and sets in the west.",
    "The notion of \"the sun rising in the east and setting in the west\" represents a highly general commonsense knowledge that does not require explicit mention in such conversations.",
    "Commonsense reasoning is crucial for natural language understanding, generating contextually relevant responses and accurately interpreting complex scenarios.",
    "The ability of commonsense reasoning is fundamental for machines to infer and navigate the complexities of the world, allowing them to reason about the world like human cognitive processes [3,29,30].To assist machines in performing commonsense reasoning, the research community has engaged in extensive work to acquire commonsense knowledge and build knowledge bases."
  ],
